('Andy Kunz', 'Andy', 'Kunz', 'Father • Husband • Hotelier', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/andydkunz', 'andydkunz', $${"about": "I am a father, husband, and hotelier with over 25 years of experience leading luxury hotels and resorts across Asia, the Middle East, North Africa, Europe, and the United States. Family and values guide my leadership style, and I believe that true hospitality starts with empathy, authenticity, and care — for our guests, our people, and our planet.\n\nCurrently, I serve as Managing Director at COMO Point Yamu in Phuket, overseeing COMO’s properties in Thailand and Bhutan. I am passionate about shaping guest journeys that go beyond accommodation, creating emotional connections and memories that last a lifetime.\n\nMy career has been defined by:\n\nRepositioning and transforming luxury resorts to deliver both financial performance and exceptional guest satisfaction.\n\nLeading large, multicultural teams with a focus on mentoring, developing future leaders, and creating a culture where people thrive.\n\nDriving sustainability through EarthCheck certification and ESG strategies that create lasting value for owners, guests, and communities.\n\nDeveloping innovative concepts integrating wellness, sustainability, and experiential travel.\n\nExploring digital transformation, including the role of agentic AI, to elevate personalization and service excellence.\n\nFluent in English, French, and German, I bring a global perspective and a deep respect for diverse cultures. I subscribe to the highest standards of honesty, loyalty, and accountability.\n\nAbove all, I believe hospitality is about more than rooms — it is about emotions, anticipation, and storytelling. My personal priority is to ensure that both my family and my teams feel supported, inspired, and empowered to leave a positive mark on the world.", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Phuket, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Phuket", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licd