('Rajat Chatterjee', 'Rajat', 'Chatterjee', 'General Manager at Chiang Mai Marriott Hotel', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/rajat010670', 'rajat010670', $${"about": "I have been in the hospitality industry since 1990. I started my career as a Management Trainee with Oberoi Hotels at the Oberoi School of Hotel Management. Subsequently I worked with Oberoi Hotels uptill 2002 and then shifted to Marriott Hotels. I am currently employed with Marriott Hotels.\n\nSpecial Achievement in Oberoi School of Hotel Management:\n\nRai Bahadur M.S. Oberoi Gold Medal for Best All Round Performance\nCertificate of Merit for Academic Excellence\n\nIn Oberoi Hotels I worked for a little over 12 years and had the opportunity to work in 3 units i.e.\n\nThe Oberoi, Grand, Kolkatta - Food & Beverage and Front Office\nThe Trident, Jaipur - Deputy General Manager\nThe Oberoi, New Delhi. - Front Office Manager and Rooms Division Manager\n\nIn Oberoi Hotels I had the opportunity to work in both Food and Beverage as well as Rooms Division field thereby giving me a very strong operational base in the hospitality industry.\n\nI have now completed more than 11 years with Marriott Hotels across 5 units i.e.\n\nJW Marriott, Mumbai - Director of Rooms and Director of Operations\nCourtyard by Marriott, Chennai - Pre Opening and Operating GM\nGoa Marriott Resort - GM\nJW Marriott, Bengaluru - Pre Opening GM\nDubai Marriott Harbour Hotel and Suites - GM\nBangkok Marriott and MEA - GM\n\nTask Force Assignments (3 Units)\n\nJW Marriott, Mumbai - 2011 (2.5 months)\nJW Marriott, Pune - 2012 (2 months)\nCY, Gurgaon - 2012 (1 month)\n\nSpecial Achievement's in Marriott Hotels:\n  \nBest Hotel Opening GM award for the Courtyard by Marriott Chennai in 2006\nLeadership Excellence Award for the Goa Marriott Resort in 2008.\n\n\n\nSpecialties: Operations\nEye for Detail and Quality Focus\nProcess Orientation\nHuman Resources and Training\nOrganisation Development", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCount