se", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQEGKU1iE7glzQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1688066609869?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=6VBY4C2VAvXLgwpnA1OTxQYyBrQwcZ7Xq83MFptTT-c", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "rob-snaith", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAA_59C8BcazgPG2JLlMnEK_NQY24uJMXukQ", "publicIdentifier": "rajat010670", "recommendations/0/context": "Rajat managed Orranut directly", "recommendations/0/date": "August 26, 2023", "recommendations/0/description": "Khun Orranut or Khun Koong as we called her at work was a phenomenal stabilizing force in the hotel. \n\nShe was working as the Director of Human Resources in this hotel and she used her people and organizational skills to ensure the team in the hotel was aligned and worked together irrespective of different departments and backgrounds to contribute to the hotels success.\n\nWhen I joined this hotel it was my first time working experience in Thailand. She helped to orient me and explained the local culture and customs. She took it upon herself to take me through a cultural sensitivity workshop to ensure I settled in well and unknowingly didn’t make culture mistakes while working with the team.\nI contribute by continued success and adaptability in Thailand to her initial investment in my orientation.\n\nShe is a people’s person, easy to get along and always a helpful soul to all. She has a background in training and uses this expertise to add value to her team and puts in effort to grow and develop her team.\n\nShe was a valuable asset to me and I believe will be for any organization and team.", "recommendations/0/name": "Orranut S.", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Human Resources Professional | Hotel", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/orranut-stephens/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAc7SgwBkb3a1NpQ1NfQGkiEPTFjvebvfG4", "recommendations/1/context": "Rajat managed Malin directly", "recommendations/1/date": "January 7, 2019", "recommendations/1/description": "Malin was responsible for managing the social media as well as conventional and digital marketing for the Bangkok Marriott Hotel, Sukhumvit Soi 57 and Marriott Executive Apartments Sukhumvit. \nMalin is a very committed and exceptional at her work and she ensured that the hotels were always trending well on social media and moved our ranking from high 30's to single digit among the top 5 hotels in Bangkok. She is an excellent team player and always willing to learn and develop herself further. She was also very committed to working and developing her team. She made efforts to assist other departments and always maintained a very positive relation with both internal and external customers.\nHer moving on is a loss for the hotel and I wish her continued success in her career.", "recommendations/1/name": "Malin Bylund", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Responsible for Malux solutions marketing & communication ● +10 years of experience ● Digital strategist", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/malin-bylund-40555330/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZ854UBOF16YAAyWuNOYrR41B33Uh0MeFQ", "recommendations/2/context": "Rajat was senior to Namrata but didn't manage Namrata directly", "recommendations/2/date": "August 16, 2009", "recommendations/2/description": "Namrata was a very dedicated and dilligent worker. She was an asset to the organisation and very good team player. She showed a very god attitude and passion to learn and develop herself. I wish her continued success in her career.", "recommendations/2/name": "Namrata Daga", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Assistant Night Manager|Front Office | Guest Experience Expert | Sales | General Administration Expert | Customer Relationship Management | Hospitality", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/namrata-daga-frontoffice-sales-administration-relationship-manager/", 