oping her team as well as contributing to the overall hotel team. She is also very focussed on developing herself profesionally. She is an asset to any organisation that she works for and i was very proud to have worked with her.", "recommendations/5/name": "Kanika Hasrat", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Hospitality Business leader Hilton Hotels| President of WICCI Hospitality| Building careers and livelihoods", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kanika-hasrat-6ab8235/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEC6iMBRC07LHzemK5ddI_zFcY_oqyKDTk", "recommendations/6/context": "Rajat managed Lakshmanan directly", "recommendations/6/date": "April 13, 2009", "recommendations/6/description": "Lakshman is a very conscientious worker. He has developed very well in the role of an FOM and is very focussed towards delivery of standards. Lakshman is a good leader and leads his team very effectively and holds them accountable for results. He is a very important member of the team and is always willing to take extra responsibility and put in extra work to help out another colleague. He is a very good team player and an asset to any team.", "recommendations/6/name": "Lakshmanan Ramanathan", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "General Manager @ Marriott Hotels | Hospitality Industry | Hotels | Pre-opening | Project Management", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lakshmanan-ramanathan-9281799/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGgVPABsx_-cB_N428VcY26Oxv5zOpVEEc", "recommendations/7/context": "Rajat was senior to V.Muthu but didn't manage V.Muthu directly", "recommendations/7/date": "December 30, 2008", "recommendations/7/description": "Muthu is a very dilligent and focussed associate and has a very personable disposition. He is easy to get along with and makes friends easily. He has made a mark in the hotel in the short time that he has worked there. He is a definite asset for the hotel and has recieved 3 promotions in the last 3 - 4 years that he has been working at Courtyard Chennai.", "recommendations/7/name": "V.Muthu Kumaran", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Seasoned and Passionate Hospitality Professional. Blockchain and Crypto Enthusiast, Investor, Trader and Affiliate.", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/v-muthu-kumaran-9513717/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFMlw0BBDM80_J7g7LevPlLZ8Rl3r6QP4Q", "recommendations/8/context": "Rajat was senior to Pancham Kaur but didn't manage Pancham Kaur directly", "recommendations/8/date": "November 29, 2008", "recommendations/8/description": "Pancham is an extremely passionate and energetic person with a very positive attitude. She is willing to learn and work really hard to improve herself. She is an asset in any team and is always willing to go the extra mile to help associates or look after guests.", "recommendations/8/name": "Pancham Kaur Narkar", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Senior General Manager Housekeeping", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pancham-kaur-narkar-5040796/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAET1pQBmpfVmKzSioexQMRh-PtWT0KK6gc", "recommendations/9/context": "Rajat was senior to Dr. Zubin but didn't manage Dr. Zubin directly", "recommendations/9/date": "November 20, 2008", "recommendations/9/description": "Zubin is a very passionate and involved Chef. He is extremely hands on and has a great relationship with his colleages and subordinates. He is a very good  team player and always willing to help other and learn new things to improve himself or his operations.", "recommendations/9/name": "Dr. Zubin D'souza, Ph.D, CHA, CFBE", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Principal and Dean of IHM-Aurangabad, Author, TEDx speaker", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/drzubinphd/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAE-gvwBDx3CDYgp8L_p8u_QJHJG_t2S0ws", "recommendations/10/context": "Rajat was senior to Sarang but didn't manage Sarang directly", "recommendations/10/date": "November 20, 2008", "recommendations/10/description": "Sarang joined the JW Marriott as an HOT and from the very beginnin he was very clear of what he wanted to achieve and the direction he wanted to take. He was ver convinced that he wanted to go in the field of Holistic well being and he gave up his hotel career to take up what was his passion. Very rarely does one see such passion, conviction and risk taking ability in young people like him. I wish him all the best in his chosen career.", "recommendations/10/name": "Sarang Nandedkar", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Assistant Registrar at Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarangnandedkar/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD0dyYBLY1qNCcnUdBn2j6B-zP0vPdYIt0", "recommendations/11/context": "Rajat was senior to Khushnooma but didn't manage Khushnooma directly", "recommendations/11/date": "September 20, 2008", "recommendations/11/description": "Khus as we call Khusnooma is an extremely passionate Marketing Communication person and she adds a lot of value to her place of work. She is very creative and is great to work with. She is open to listening to others inputs and working together with the team to create high impact communication and marketing initiatives. I have now worked with Khush over three job roles and she has consistently added value in each one of them and contributed immensley to the needs of the organisation.", "recommendations/11/name": "Khushnooma Kapadia", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Vice President - Marketing; South Asia at Marriott International Inc", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/khushnoomakapadia/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHOy1ABDNCXYVCH_clGCWbhIAbeZPOTzJ0", "recommendations/12/context": "Rajat was senior to Anjali but didn't manage Anjali directly", "recommendations/12/date": "September 12, 2008", "recommendations/12/description": "Anjali is very passionate about her work and is a good team player. Always willing to think out of the box and also contribute to the overall vision and mission of the organisation. She added a lot of value to the hotel during the opening crucial phase of the hotel.", "recommendations/12/name": "Anjali P.", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Founder and CEO at Aquilar Strategic Services", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anjalipais/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAELLEYBpPF2cqO0RLuujOOcx_bf462EIUg", "recommendations/13/context": "Rajat was senior to Mielle but didn't manage Mielle directly", "recommendations/13/date": "September 8, 2008", "recommendations/13/description": "Mielle is an absolute Gem to work with, she is extremely helpful, full of good cheer and always willing to go the extra mile. She has a fantastic rapport with almost everyone I know and is a thorough HR professional. It was a pleasure to work with Mielle and i would really look forward to working with her again sometime in the future.", "recommendations/13/name": "Mielle Batliwala", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "VP - Human Resources at Sarovar Hotels (India’s 3rd Largest Hospitality Chain) | Ex-Marriott International", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mielle-batliwala-9128682/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAB7oR4BvoV0YXhXajP5mnsJVf5gMduq4Fg", "recommendations/14/context": "Rajat worked with L. Aruna on the same team", "recommendations/14/date": "June 30, 2008", "recommendations/14/description": "Aruna and I worked together at The Oberoi, New Delhi. Aruna was very good at her job and always helpful. She was a good team player and had a fantastic sense of humor and presence of mind. It was great working with Aruna as she was very helpful and extremely creative in her field. She was an outstanding Marketing Communications Manager and I look for more opportunities to work with her again.", "recommendations/14/name": "L. Aruna Dhir", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "Author of Best-selling Memoir 'Hotel Adventures with the Stars,' International Hospitality Writer, Communications Specialist, GSE USA 2001, CSC Australia 2003", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arunadhir/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD3OZwBAcRGe_hehiDh-u_iSvMaHosdHAU", "recommendations/15/context": "Rajat managed Vyshnavi directly", "recommendations/15/date": "June 22, 2008", "recommendations/15/description": "Vyshnavi was a pleasure to work with. She was looking after Marketing Communication at the Courtyard by Marriott and her positive attitude and creative inputs really helped us establish the brand and hotel in Chennai. She is very passionate about her work and likes to take up new challenges and never shirks from additional responsibilities. She is a great team player and was an asset to my team. I look forward to another opportunity to work with Vyshnavi.", "recommendations/15/name": "Vyshnavi Kuppuswamy", "recommendations/15/subtitle": "Cultural Ambassador l Entrepreneur l Brand Management | Content Creation | Hospitality Marketing | Communication Strategy", "recommendations/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vyshnavikuppuswamy/", "recommendations/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADMoiABSlrK-sWAF1OI9CLV8vUw7bxOFQs", "recommendations/16/context": "Rajat managed Pankaj directly", "recommendations/16/date": "June 12, 2008", "recommendations/16/description": "Pankaj and I worked together when he was an Airport Manager for The Oberoi, New Delhi. Even then it was very apparant that Pankaj was very pasionate about what he did. He did a very good job of setting up the Airport divison and managed his team as well as working out of an external environment really well. Due to his ability to develop himself he was further offered a role in Sales and Marketing.", "recommendations/16/name": "Pankaj Malik", "recommendations/16/subtitle": "Business Leader", "recommendations/16/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pankajmalik/", "recommendations/16/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABkFzEBqeBBbry9hbttZM3rVGWgJhVDbyk", "recommendations/17/context": "Rajat was senior to Prakash but didn't manage Prakash directly", "recommendations/17/date": "June 12, 2008", "recommendations/17/description": "Prakash is very good chef and an excellent team player. Prakash is a very passionate chef and has very good skill set. He is an extremely creative person and a very good trainer. He has a great attitude and always willing to go the extra mile. He leads by example and is a true motivator and leader for others to follow in the kitchen.", "recommendations/17/name": "Prakash Jayadevan", "recommendations/17/subtitle": "COO at The Residency Group of Hotels", "recommendations/17/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/prakashjayadevan/", "recommendations/17/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADDL6wBD941Lb7xl6UCPKs0WC7hVXUGgWI", "recommendations/18/context": "Rajat managed Partha directly", "recommendations/18/date": "June 12, 2008", "recommendations/18/description": "Partha is a great professional and an asset to any organisation. He is a very good people's person and is an extremely hands on manager. Partha has a fantastic attitude and takes his work very seriously. He is very well liked by his team, his peers as well as his superiors. Partha is very dilligent and focussed on the job and always willing to understand another point of view. He contributes in leadership forums in a constructive manner. Partha shows keen desire to develop his team and himself all the time and he is very open to change. I would really like another opportunity to be able to work with him again.", "recommendations/18/name": "Partha Basak", "recommendations/18/subtitle": "Senior Director - Finance Operations | Luxury Brands - Middle East, Qatar, Kuwait & Turkiye | Marriott International", "recommendations/18/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/partha-basak-5713488/", "recommendations/18/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF5YSUBDWNwz0PsfKDKqN3XUjcvEszujGY", "recommendations/19/context": "Rajat managed Vikas directly", "recommendations/19/date": "May 27, 2008", "recommendations/19/description": "Vikas joined the Courtyard by Marriott, Chennai as an opening team member in the designation of F&B Manager. He was responsible for setting up the entire F&B division. Vikas did a great job and within a year of his tenure in Chennai he was promoted to Director of F&B. Vikas not only managed F&B operations but also had additional responsibility of Loss Prevention and contributed whole heartedly for the betterment of the hotel by contributing to every departments performance. He was the number 2 in the hotel and was officiating in the GM's absence. Vikas is a very keen learner and always open to change. He mantains excellent relationships with his Guests, Superiors, Associates and Peers. Vikas was instrumental in the success of the Courtyard by Marriott in Chennai. His acumen in Finance is excellent and he has great skills in presentations. He is a great team member and i would like the oportunity to work with him again.", "recommendations/19/name": "Vikas Malik", "recommendations/19/subtitle": "Marriott International", "recommendations/19/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vikas-malik-0976665/", "recommendations/19/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD8pvMBr9npolpuzt9urj4KAinjDofuBWY", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Hagop reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "June 29, 2015", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I have worked with Rajat for almost two years. He is a kind of a person from whom you will learn a lot. He will share his experiences with anyone who is having a challenge and try to find a solution to it. His words are:always involve the impacted in decision making\". He always details everything, simplifies it and prioritizes acts. Very transparent, straight to the point, challenges his team, fun to work with. He always repeated \"No one will remember the second place winner, always the top winner is remembered\". Last but not least, he is a \"Work Hard, Play Hard\" sort of a person, who is devoted into his job, so passionate that he does everything with is heart. Because of all of the above, he deserved and won the General Manager of the Year for Marriott International Middle East and Africa Continent Award and also nested the hotel he was managing, The Marriott Harbour Hotel and Suites, Dubai as the Hotel of the year among many other global and regional awards the hotel team won. A role model and a person with whom I would love to work again anywhere, anytime. Thank you Rajat for teaching me.     ", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Hagop Tchaparian", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Experienced Hospitality & Luxury Lifestyle Leader", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hagop-tchaparian-04b89411/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJxpDsB5lNTDPddx7hyPQ510tp87H0_9FQ", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Rajat was senior to Pardeep but didn't manage Pardeep directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "October 9, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Great General Manager.has been a role model for all his employees.Man with great enthu,eye for detailing,strong leadership,charming personality & always proactive.It was pleasure working with him and definitely will look forward to work with him again.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Pardeep Siwach", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Hospitality Professional", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pardeep-siwach-43767223/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAATnPusBNanEOhAPMsG_b7h9V0hpMFPY0PQ", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Vyshnavi reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "November 26, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "A great team leader!! It was a pleasure to work with Rajat! He is extremely knowledgeable about every sphere and always had some value add to the job at hand. A great motivator he was also the first one who would come out with genuine appreciation for a job well done. A tough task master, he is demanding and accepts nothing but the best and this definitely kept us on our feet. I owe all that I have learnt in this industry to him he has been my guide and mentor. Thank you Rajat for your support and I look forward to working with you soon...", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Vyshnavi Kuppuswamy", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Cultural Ambassador l Entrepreneur l Brand Management | Content Creation | Hospitality Marketing | Communication Strategy", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vyshnavikuppuswamy/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADMoiABSlrK-sWAF1OI9CLV8vUw7bxOFQs", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Rajat was senior to Pancham Kaur but didn't manage Pancham Kaur directly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "September 14, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I have not been reporting to Rajat directly but have worked with him for about a years time. Rajat is very hard working and a true professional. Rajat has been one person whom i have actually seen working and managing his personal and professional relationships very well. I admire his sense of humour and his eye for detail. He could show us and get us to those goals which we would have thought as not achievable. He would judge each ones capacity and have the person to achieve the best. He was a very poeples person, there is not one instance that i would have forgotten along with him. I have learnt a lot from him. Miss him very much. And look forward to working with him again in future.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Pancham Kaur Narkar", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Senior General Manager Housekeeping", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pancham-kaur-narkar-5040796/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAET1pQBmpfVmKzSioexQMRh-PtWT0KK6gc", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Sarang worked with Rajat on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "September 13, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Rajat was an excellent team leader and a Manager who could empathise with his staff.  The best part of his personality  was that he was approachable and cooperative. I got his full cooperation when I had expressed my will to switch and train in the Spa department from Front office (In the Rooms Division).", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Sarang Nandedkar", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Assistant Registrar at Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarangnandedkar/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD0dyYBLY1qNCcnUdBn2j6B-zP0vPdYIt0", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "L. Aruna worked with Rajat but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "July 3, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "I have found Rajat to be an extremely affable person and an excellent manager, with a finger on the pulse of the product, the people and processes. A sharp intellect, pleasant nature and a lot of energy and drive define Rajat aptly. Rajat's penchant for thinking in superlatives will always stand him in good stead!", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "L. Aruna Dhir", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Author of Best-selling Memoir 'Hotel Adventures with the Stars,' International Hospitality Writer, Communications Specialist, GSE USA 2001, CSC Australia 2003", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arunadhir/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD3OZwBAcRGe_hehiDh-u_iSvMaHosdHAU", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Rajat was senior to Prakash but didn't manage Prakash directly", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "July 1, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Rajat is a very focussed manager and believes in  attention to detail. He invests considerable time in grooming his juniors and helps them considerably to improve upon their knowledge and skills. His eye for detail is comendable and is truly someone to learn from", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Prakash Jayadevan", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "COO at The Residency Group of Hotels", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/prakashjayadevan/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADDL6wBD941Lb7xl6UCPKs0WC7hVXUGgWI", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Anjali reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "July 1, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "Rajat's passion for his people was what made it a pleasure to work with him. Yes, he was instrumental in the establishment of Courtyard Marriott in Chennai right from scratch in terms of systems and processes (and did a fabulous job of that). But to me, the kind of culture he established there was what made him outstanding as a leader. He was committed, creative, approachable, fun loving, passionate and yet focussed on excellence in service delivery, and that was the kind of work culture that he fostered. Truly a pleasure working with him.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Anjali P.", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "Founder and CEO at Aquilar Strategic Services", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anjalipais/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAELLEYBpPF2cqO0RLuujOOcx_bf462EIUg", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "Mielle worked with Rajat on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "July 1, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "Rajat Chatterjee, or RC as we know him, is someone who needs no introduction !! He is, by far, one of the most dynamic, demanding; yet supportive to the hilt, creative, passionate & inspiring leaders I've worked with. One word that fits all - perfectionist, and he settles for nothing less. He leads by example, involves his team in his vision and decisions, and.he truly brings out the best in his people. Most definitely one GM that I'd like to work with in future.", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "Mielle Batliwala", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "VP - Human Resources at Sarovar Hotels (India’s 3rd Largest Hospitality Chain) | Ex-Marriott International", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mielle-batliwala-9128682/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAB7oR4BvoV0YXhXajP5mnsJVf5gMduq4Fg", "recommendationsReceived/9/context": "Jamshed worked with Rajat but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/9/date": "June 29, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/9/description": "I think Rajat needs no introduction - he has been a wonderful colleagues always willing to to take the first step forward and show initiative. he is an analytical thinker and has always put rationality before emotion and shown courage and patience during challenging times. His gentle smile and warmth towards his colleagues and passion towards service is someeting I remember from our times together. he has in him to make every person special no matter who he or she is and I think that is rare in this world.", "recommendationsReceived/9/name": "Jamshed Chhor", "recommendationsReceived/9/subtitle": "Manager - Organisation Development and Training", "recommendationsReceived/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jamshed-chhor-4330a81/", "recommendationsReceived/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAw8mcBWQRJVLzFc7o-KMNFWPOgpWHncLY", "recommendationsReceived/10/context": "Rattan managed Rajat directly", "recommendationsReceived/10/date": "June 28, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/10/description": "Rajat was a wonderful Rooms Division Manager-his focus on guests process,internal systems and financials was complete. Extremely good with his team he contributed significantly to the success of the rooms division of the hotel for the years that he spent there.", "recommendationsReceived/10/name": "Rattan Keswani", "recommendationsReceived/10/subtitle": "President-Trident Hotels", "recommendationsReceived/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rattan-keswani-0325635/", "recommendationsReceived/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD4xmYBnnnXmUMVeAWdedFKrzczpLNnez4", "recommendationsReceived/11/context": "Rayomund reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/11/date": "June 24, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/11/description": "Rajat Chatterjee is highly respected by his co-workers for his willingnes to anyone anytime he can.Rajat is been instrumental in helping the company by his cost saving procedures. Rajat during a very short period of his time with Goa Marriott Resort India is being doing an amazing impact on the appearance and financial turn around at the property.\nRajat is very well organised, diligent in his paper work, easily reachable for all his associates irrespective of their designation.\n\nWith great respect\nRayomund Pardiwalla\nChef de cuisine\nWanhao chinese restaurant\nGoa Marriott Resort \nIndia", "recommendationsReceived/11/name": "Rayomund Pardiwalla", "recommendationsReceived/11/subtitle": "food n beverage at GOA Marriott resort India", "recommendationsReceived/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rayomund-pardiwalla-2a59628/", "recommendationsReceived/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGQoR0BeoT3abXer5SCYc6i8BuzumGY-Rk", "recommendationsReceived/12/context": "Christopher reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/12/date": "June 24, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/12/description": "Working with Rajat Chatterjee was always an enriching experience. Rajat is competent and thorough, his organisational skills and fine grasp of detail would take him to hold a key position in any large Organisation.", "recommendationsReceived/12/name": "Chri