etail oriented manager who aims at exceeding guest's expectations. His ability to be a team member has always brought excellent returns.", "recommendationsReceived/15/name": "Pankaj Malik", "recommendationsReceived/15/subtitle": "Business Leader", "recommendationsReceived/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pankajmalik/", "recommendationsReceived/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABkFzEBqeBBbry9hbttZM3rVGWgJhVDbyk", "recommendationsReceived/16/context": "Hans-Georg managed Rajat directly", "recommendationsReceived/16/date": "June 15, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/16/description": "Rajat was very detailed oriented and showed great initiative. He very quickly adjusted to the Marriott Culture and became a strong supporter of all key initiatives. He was instrumental in moving from the pre-opening phase to building crtitical support structures in the Rooms department and delivering outstanding customer experiences. He is very tenacious and has a good rapport with his associates.\nIt was a pleasure to work with Rajat and I wish him well for his future.", "recommendationsReceived/16/name": "Hans-Georg Roehrbein", "recommendationsReceived/16/subtitle": "EXECUTIVE PARTNER MMG is a global powerhouse consulting and management firm that is specialized in m at mmg - management & consulting; Certified in Hospitality Commercial Strategy", "recommendationsReceived/16/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hansroehrbein/", "recommendationsReceived/16/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEE9wgBC_L-zL1kabwrIT_Z0CLaAFDwoIg", "recommendationsReceived/17/context": "Partha reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/17/date": "June 12, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/17/description": "Rajat has been a great leader. He could inspire and motivate his team and colleagues to come out of the \"closed box\" and perform. His extra ordinary people skills, his indepth knowledge about hotel operations and excellent team spirits has put Rajat as one of the best in his job role as General Manager of a Hospitality Giant.", "recommendationsReceived/17/name": "Partha Basak", "recommendationsReceived/17/subtitle": "Senior Director - Finance Operations | Luxury Brands - Middle East, Qatar, Kuwait & Turkiye | Marriott International", "recommendationsReceived/17/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/partha-basak-5713488/", "recommendationsReceived/17/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF5YSUBDWNwz0PsfKDKqN3XUjcvEszujGY", "recommendationsReceived/18/context": "Vikas reported directly to Rajat", "recommendationsReceived/18/date": "May 27, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/18/description": "\"Devil is in Detail\" the meaning became clear while working with him in Chennai. He is a great task master and very people’s person and knows how to balance the two. \n\nWorking with him was good fun and a great learning experience and I would say it was one of the best openings I have ever done, both personally and professionally.\n\nIt was like a jigsaw puzzle and he kept putting pieces together and finally the picture that came out was a perfect “balance score card” (for those who don’t know it’s a Marriott term) hotel.\n\nI wish him all the best and good luck for future and would love to work again with him - sometime.", "recommendationsReceived/18/name": "Vikas Malik", "recommendationsReceived/18/subtitle": "Marriott International", "recommendationsReceived/18/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vikas-malik-0976665/", "recommendationsReceived/18/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD8pvMBr9npolpuzt9urj4KAinjDofuBWY", "skills/0/title": "Hotels", "skills/1/title": "Revenue Analysis", "skills/2/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/3/title": "Organizational Development", "skills/4/title": "Hospitality Industry", "skills/5/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/6/title": "Front Office", "skills/7/title": "Yield Management", "skills/8/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/9/title": "Rooms Division", "skills/10/title": "Banquets", "skills/11/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/12/title": "Restaurants